00:54:43,728 --> 00:54:44,613
- I'm sorry.

905
00:54:48,270 --> 00:54:50,133
- No big deal, it's just a swab.

906
00:54:52,470 --> 00:54:56,673
So what was it like spending
the night in the slammer?

907
00:54:58,719 --> 00:55:01,253
- (snickers) Awful.

908
00:55:03,050 --> 00:55:04,140
But to tell you the truth,

909
00:55:04,140 --> 00:55:06,390
it's not the first time
I've been in holding.

910
00:55:07,830 --> 00:55:08,663
- What'd you do?

911
00:55:08,663 --> 00:55:11,360
- (laughs) Well some
friends and I got in trouble

912
00:55:11,360 --> 00:55:13,203
for vandalizing school property.

913
00:55:14,550 --> 00:55:17,470
This feminist speaker came to campus,

914
00:55:17,470 --> 00:55:19,330
and one of the sororities didn't approve,

915
00:55:19,330 --> 00:55:21,150
so they had her banned.

916
00:55:21,150 --> 00:55:22,963
- So you guys trashed their nest?

917
00:55:24,140 --> 00:55:26,873
- It was more like we
tried to burn it down.

918
00:55:27,930 --> 00:55:29,327
- You burned down their house?

919
00:55:29,327 --> 00:55:31,490
- (laughs) No, just the shrubbery.

920
00:55:31,490 --> 00:55:34,140
The fire department got to
it before it could spread.

921
00:55:35,500 --> 00:55:38,063
It was a huge mistake,
nothing I'm proud of.

922
00:55:40,490 --> 00:55:43,623
- So are you worried about the hearing?

923
00:55:47,610 --> 00:55:48,443
- No.

924
00:55:48,443 --> 00:55:50,563
I don't want you to worry about it either.

925
00:55:51,740 --> 00:55:54,630
You have a lot of other
things to focus on.

926
00:55:54,630 --> 00:55:56,040
And we wouldn't want your opponent

927
00:55:56,040 --> 00:55:57,640
to think that you're distracted.

928
00:56:07,230 --> 00:56:08,680
- Mom's pretty pissed at you.

929
00:56:12,250 --> 00:56:13,650
- She has every right to be.

930
00:56:15,171 --> 00:56:16,004
So do you.

931
00:56:20,153 --> 00:56:21,320
I love you.

932
00:56:21,320 --> 00:56:22,852
See ya in the morning.

933
00:56:22,852 --> 00:56:24,117
- Good night.
- Night.

934
00:56:24,117 --> 00:56:26,700
(gentle music)

935
00:56:39,537 --> 00:56:43,454
I'm just getting some
linen for the guest room.

936
00:57:02,390 --> 00:57:03,223
Hey.

937
00:57:04,120 --> 00:57:04,953
- Hey.

938
00:57:08,370 --> 00:57:09,780
I don't know what'll happen between us

939
00:57:09,780 --> 00:57:11,533
when this is all settled, but ...

940
00:57:15,570 --> 00:57:17,500
There's too much at stake to
let you go through this alone,

941
00:57:17,500 --> 00:57:19,700
so you've got my support
for the time being.

942
00:57:22,240 --> 00:57:23,120
I'll do what I can to help,

943
00:57:23,120 --> 00:57:25,253
but that's all I can give you.

944
00:57:48,630 --> 00:57:49,850
- [Audrey] Morning.

945
00:57:49,850 --> 00:57:51,070
- You ready to go?

946
00:57:51,070 --> 00:57:54,110
- I'm not scheduled to
meet Aaron until noon.

947
00:57:54,110 --> 00:57:55,460
- I think it's best if we went in

948
00:57:55,460 --> 00:57:57,130
a different direction for this one.

949
00:57:57,130 --> 00:57:58,200
- [Audrey] But he's our attorney.

950
00:57:58,200 --> 00:57:59,820
- Just trust me.

951
00:57:59,820 --> 00:58:01,070
- [Blythe] You know we love you,

952
00:58:01,070 --> 00:58:02,520
but Neal, I can't keep covering

953
00:58:02,520 --> 00:58:03,510
your end of the timeshare.

954
00:58:03,510 --> 00:58:05,080
That shit's gettin' too expensive.

955
00:58:05,080 --> 00:58:06,330
- [Neal] I know, it's just that

956
00:58:06,330 --> 00:58:08,300
alimony's kicking my ass right now.

957
00:58:08,300 --> 00:58:10,920
- [Blythe] Yeah, well alimony
is a huge bitch to feed.

958
00:58:10,920 --> 00:58:12,520
I'm no stranger to it.

959
00:58:12,520 --> 00:58:15,250
My first husband was a struggling
artist, if you remember.

960
00:58:15,250 --> 00:58:16,470
- I do.
- Now keep in mind,

961
00:58:16,470 --> 00:58:17,713
I led the litter too, so.

962
00:58:17,713 --> 00:58:19,630
- [Neal] I hear ya loud and clear, Blythe.

963
00:58:19,630 --> 00:58:20,610
I'll give you a call next week.

964
00:58:20,610 --> 00:58:21,860
- You do that.

965
00:58:21,860 --> 00:58:22,853
And take care.

966
00:58:28,560 --> 00:58:30,780
Carrie, it's been years!
(phone rings)

967
00:58:30,780 --> 00:58:31,620
How ya been?

968
00:58:31,620 --> 00:58:32,743
- Good.

969
00:58:32,743 --> 00:58:34,340
- [Blythe] (laughs) You look it!

970
00:58:34,340 --> 00:58:35,173
- Thanks.

971
00:58:35,173 --> 00:58:36,006
- So what are you doing here?

972
00:58:36,006 --> 00:58:37,600
Aren't you usually on
the air about this time?

973
00:58:37,600 --> 00:58:39,670
- Yeah, I took the morning off.

974
00:58:39,670 --> 00:58:41,280
- Everything okay?

975
00:58:41,280 --> 00:58:43,890
- Yeah, Blythe, this is my wife, Audrey.

976
00:58:43,890 --> 00:58:45,520
- It's nice to meet you Audrey.

977
00:58:45,520 --> 00:58:46,903
- [Audrey] Nice to meet you.

978
00:58:48,190 --> 00:58:50,490
- Why don't you two come
on back to my office.

979
00:58:58,140 --> 00:59:01,163
That's, (sighs) it's quite a story.

980
00:59:02,500 --> 00:59:05,333
Extremely complicated, it is.

981
00:59:07,020 --> 00:59:09,030
And you're not speaking
theoretically, I assume.

982
00:59:09,030 --> 00:59:13,270
You literally purchased
another woman's child.

983
00:59:13,270 --> 00:59:14,600
- She rescued him.

984
00:59:14,600 --> 00:59:15,433
- Right.

985
00:59:18,270 --> 00:59:19,533
See, here's the thing.

986
00:59:21,500 --> 00:59:22,770
Even with the mother's consent,

987
00:59:22,770 --> 00:59:24,600
it would be difficult to convince

988
00:59:24,600 --> 00:59:26,870
