1027
01:01:21,020 --> 01:01:22,470
- So what am I supposed to do now?

1028
01:01:22,470 --> 01:01:24,910
I mean, I spent the last
10 years raising him.

1029
01:01:24,910 --> 01:01:27,040
I can't afford for her
to lose the case either.

1030
01:01:27,040 --> 01:01:28,410
- I'm sorry, I really am.

1031
01:01:28,410 --> 01:01:31,210
But there's nothing I can do.

1032
01:01:31,210 --> 01:01:33,990
I know I've developed a
rather incautious reputation

1033
01:01:33,990 --> 01:01:35,350
throughout my career, but even I like

1034
01:01:35,350 --> 01:01:36,633
to win from time to time.

1035
01:01:37,480 --> 01:01:38,423
Nothing personal.

1036
01:01:41,520 --> 01:01:42,353
- Right.

1037
01:01:48,020 --> 01:01:50,687
(door slamming)

1038
01:01:57,112 --> 01:01:59,021
(somber music)

1039
01:01:59,021 --> 01:02:01,938
(Audrey sniffling)

1040
01:02:06,050 --> 01:02:08,120
I thought she'd be able to help us.

1041
01:02:08,120 --> 01:02:08,953
I'm sorry.

1042
01:02:14,460 --> 01:02:17,350
We'll find good
representation though, okay?

1043
01:02:17,350 --> 01:02:18,183
I promise.

1044
01:02:30,451 --> 01:02:31,870
Mm hmm.

1045
01:02:31,870 --> 01:02:35,160
Yeah well with Blythe's
appeal, they don't have time.

1046
01:02:35,160 --> 01:02:36,283
Yeah sure, honesty?

1047
01:02:40,080 --> 01:02:41,313
Okay, thanks Rosie.

