- After you were hired for this case,

1334
01:21:41,020 --> 01:21:44,130
where did your investigation begin?

1335
01:21:44,130 --> 01:21:45,560
- At St. Gregory Hospital.

1336
01:21:45,560 --> 01:21:47,220
It was the last place
Valerie had been seen

1337
01:21:47,220 --> 01:21:49,710
before she returned home a year later.

1338
01:21:49,710 --> 01:21:52,883
- And what sort of information
did you come across there?

1339
01:21:54,060 --> 01:21:55,083
- Nothing really.

1340
01:21:56,120 --> 01:21:57,630
The staff had changed significantly,

1341
01:21:57,630 --> 01:22:00,410
so at that point, I had to rely heavily

1342
01:22:00,410 --> 01:22:03,410
on the hospital's records for
the information that I needed.

1343
01:22:03,410 --> 01:22:05,890
- Was that helpful to you?

1344
01:22:05,890 --> 01:22:07,372
- Not at the beginning.

1345
01:22:07,372 --> 01:22:08,920
A lot of the records were rearranged

1346
01:22:08,920 --> 01:22:11,010
and some of them appeared to be missing.

1347
01:22:11,010 --> 01:22:12,460
- [Richard] Missing, you say.

1348
01:22:13,610 --> 01:22:14,503
- That's correct.

1349
01:22:15,350 --> 01:22:17,450
- So what did you do then?

1350
01:22:17,450 --> 01:22:19,430
- I investigated the
hospital for another week,

1351
01:22:19,430 --> 01:22:21,560
and then Valerie requested that I help her

1352
01:22:21,560 --> 01:22:24,340
with a couple of other
investigators on another case.

1353
01:22:24,340 --> 01:22:25,243
- Why was that?

1354
01:22:26,470 --> 01:22:28,230
- Her campaign started
receiving the attention

1355
01:22:28,230 --> 01:22:30,380
of a lot of others with
similar situations.

1356
01:22:31,810 --> 01:22:32,810
Nothing quite like hers,

1357
01:22:32,810 --> 01:22:35,840
but similar in that they were
missing children as well.

1358
01:22:35,840 --> 01:22:40,210
- And within those nine
years through her campaign,

1359
01:22:40,210 --> 01:22:45,210
how many families were reunited
with their missing children?

1360
01:22:45,260 --> 01:22:46,720
- [Matt] Seven.

1361
01:22:46,720 --> 01:22:48,920
- Seven, that's remarkable.

1362
01:22:48,920 --> 01:22:49,990
- Yes it is.

1363
01:22:49,990 --> 01:22:52,440
I'm damn proud to be a part of it.

1364
01:22:52,440 --> 01:22:53,483
- You should be.

1365
01:22:54,950 --> 01:22:59,350
So what caused you to
reevaluate Valerie's case?

1366
01:22:59,350 --> 01:23:01,340
- I started to feel guilty.

1367
01:23:01,340 --> 01:23:03,870
All of us did, because
we were helpin' others

1368
01:23:03,870 --> 01:23:05,170
find their missin' loved ones,

1369
01:23:05,170 --> 01:23:07,833
and Valerie's son was
still out there somewhere.

1370
01:23:08,690 --> 01:23:11,210
- Was she ever bitter about that?

1371
01:23:11,210 --> 01:23:14,460
- No, she was always callin' the shots.

1372
01:23:14,460 --> 01:23:15,910
She often talked about how it was

1373
01:23:15,910 --> 01:23:18,249
a rewarding experience for her.

1374
01:23:18,249 --> 01:23:20,280
I think she felt indebted
to her supporters.

1375
01:23:20,280 --> 01:23:21,890
I made it a priority though

1376
01:23:21,890 --> 01:23:23,610
to see to it that it
was just as fulfilling

1377
01:23:23,610 --> 01:23:25,560
for her as it was for everyone else.

1378
01:23:25,560 --> 01:23:30,330
- So that's when you decided
to return to the hospital

1379
01:23:30,330 --> 01:23:32,620
and continue your investigation?

1380
01:23:32,620 --> 01:23:34,000
- Yeah.

1381
01:23:34,000 --> 01:23:37,020
I was givin' the records
another look-through,

1382
01:23:37,020 --> 01:23:39,880
and I realized that of all
the staff that had moved on,

1383
01:23:39,880 --> 01:23:42,310
the defendant was the
only one that relocated.

1384
01:23:42,310 --> 01:23:44,730
So I discovered her whereabouts,

1385
01:23:44,730 --> 01:23:47,820
and that's when we reached
out to our contact in Chicago.

1386
01:23:47,820 --> 01:23:49,723
- Thank you Mr. Collins.

1387
01:23:51,700 --> 01:23:53,343
No further questions Your Honor.

1388
01:23:56,980 --> 01:23:58,083
- Mr. Collins,

1389
01:23:59,020 --> 01:24:01,920
for a minute there I thought
your statement was reputable.

1390
01:24:01,920 --> 01:24:04,920
In fact, you nearly
escaped cross-examination.

1391
01:24:04,920 --> 01:24:06,900
But then, you mentioned

1392
01:24:06,900 --> 01:24:10,170
that in your first investigation
at St. Gregory's Hospital,

1393
01:24:10,170 --> 01:24:11,860
there were documents that had been

1394
01:24:11,860 --> 01:24:14,540
rearranged or misplaced, correct?

1395
01:24:14,540 --> 01:24:16,000
- Correct.

1396
01:24:16,000 --> 01:24:18,250
- But I'm pretty sure that I possess

1397
01:24:18,250 --> 01:24:21,310
the same hospital records
that you investigated.

1398
01:24:21,310 --> 01:24:22,143
Am I right?

1399
01:24:22,143 --> 01:24:23,890
- I'm sure you do.

1400
01:24:23,890 --> 01:24:25,130
- So do you think the prosecution

1401
01:24:25,130 --> 01:24:27,070
would send me faulty documents?

1402
01:24:27,070 --> 01:24:28,390
- Of course not.

1403
01:24:28,390 --> 01:24:30,940
- Well the hospital records that I possess

1404
01:24:30,940 --> 01:24:34,605
are pretty consistent
for the last 20 years.

1405
01:24:34,605 --> 01:24:35,438
- So? (chuckles)

1406
01:24:35,438 --> 01:24:36,320
what's the problem?

1407
01:24:37,220 --> 01:24:39,690
- The problem is that the jury

1408
01:24:39,690 --> 01:24:41,890
is hanging on your every word.

1409
01:24:41,890 --> 01:24:43,360
And you're making cryptic statements

1410
01:24:43,360 --> 01:24:45,840
that incriminate my
client when you suggest

1411
01:24:45,840 --> 01:24:48,810
that files have been
rearranged or misplaced.

1412
01:24:48,810 --> 01:24:50,670
You made the impression that my client

1413
01:24:50,670 --> 01:24:51,530
may have been responsible.

1414
01:24:51,530 --> 01:24:53,347
- I never said that.

1415
01:24:53,347 --> 01:24:54,890
It coulda been a hospital
error for all I know.

1416
01:24:54,890 --> 01:24:57,100
- Then let the record show that my client

1417
01:24:57,100 --> 01:24:58,730
had nothing to do with the rearrangement

1418
01:24:58,730 --> 01:25:01,500
or misplacement of hospital documents.

1419
01:25:01,500 --> 01:25:03,850
But as Mr. Collins just implied,

1420
01:25:03,850 --> 01:25:06,290
it was due to the negligence
of St. Gregory Hospital,

1421
01:25:06,290 --> 01:25:08,800
and see if that doesn't get
ya a defamation lawsuit.

1422
01:25:08,800 --> 01:25:11,240
- Objection, Your Honor.

1423
01:25:11,240 --> 01:25:14,160
She's embellishing my witness's statement.

1424
01:25:14,160 --> 01:25:15,023
- Sustained.

1425
01:25:16,070 --> 01:25:18,120
Cut it out, Counselor.

1426
01:25:18,120 --> 01:25:20,300
And let the record show

1427
01:25:20,300 --> 01:25:22,960
that nothing in the witness's statement

1428
01:25:22,960 --> 01:25:25,230
is denigrating to St. Gregory Hospital.

1429
01:25:25,230 --> 01:25:26,923
- No further questions, Your Honor.

1430
01:25:28,290 --> 01:25:30,823
- Any further questions for
this witness, Counselor?

1431
01:25:32,010 --> 01:25:33,430
- No further questions, Your Honor.

1432
01:25:33,430 --> 01:25:34,820
- Then we'll break for recess.

1433
01:25:34,820 --> 01:25:36,708
This hearing will proceed in one hour.

1434
01:25:36,708 --> 01:25:39,208
(gavel banging)

1435
01:25:45,170 --> 01:25:46,040
- Mom!

1436
01:25:46,040 --> 01:25:47,190
- [Audrey] Hey sweetie.

1437
01:25:49,170 --> 01:25:50,003
- Hi.
- Hi.

1438
01:25:50,900 --> 01:25:52,830
- How you holdin' up in there?

1439
01:25:52,830 --> 01:25:54,100
- Fine.

1440
01:25:54,100 --> 01:25:54,933
- Hey guys.
(phone rings)

1441
01:25:54,933 --> 01:25:55,766
- Hi.

1442
01:25:55,766 --> 01:25:57,220
- Oh, I need to take this.

1443
01:25:57,220 --> 01:25:58,376
I'll see you in an hour.

1444
01:25:58,376 --> 01:25:59,709
- [Audrey] Okay.

1445
01:26:00,928 --> 01:26:02,840
- Do you wanna grab lunch?

1446
01:26:02,840 --> 01:26:04,180
- [Audrey] I don't have
much of an appetite.

1447
01:26:04,180 --> 01:26:06,280
Why don't you guys grab lunch without me.

1448
01:26:06,280 --> 01:26:07,470
- You sure?
- Yeah, I'll grab

1449
01:26:07,470 --> 01:26:08,590
something later.

1450
01:26:08,590 --> 01:26:09,423
I'm fine.

1451
01:26:10,270 --> 01:26:11,300
- [Carrie] See you soon.

1452
01:26:11,300 --> 01:26:12,510
- [Audrey] Okay.

1453
01:26:12,510 --> 01:26:13,343
- Bye.

1454
01:26:13,343 --> 01:26:14,176
- [Audrey] Bye.

1455
01:26:20,720 --> 01:26:23,820
- And how long was it before you realized

1456
01:26:23,820 --> 01:26:28,820
that the signatures on the
adoption forms were inauthentic?

1457
01:26:29,100 --> 01:26:30,230
- Right away.

1458
01:26:30,230 --> 01:26:33,000
The signature that Valerie used
to sign all of her documents

1459
01:26:33,000 --> 01:26:36,320
was different from the
signature on the adoption forms.

1460
01:26:36,320 --> 01:26:37,153
- How different?

1461
01:26:38,620 --> 01:26:39,453
- Significantly.

1462
01:26:41,060 --> 01:26:43,260
The defendant signed Valerie's full name

1463
01:26:43,260 --> 01:26:44,600
on the adoption forms,

1464
01:26:44,600 --> 01:26:49,430
but Valerie normally just
signed her name as V Whit.

1465
01:26:49,430 --> 01:26:51,573
- How did you confirm this?

1466
01:26:53,370 --> 01:26:55,610
- Several signatures from Valerie,

1467
01:26:55,610 --> 01:26:58,530
including the signature on
the adoption forms were sent

1468
01:26:58,530 --> 01:27:02,300
to a local forensic document
examiner for analysis.

1469
01:27:02,300 --> 01:27:06,590
- Which proved that the
signatures on those adoption forms

1470
01:27:06,590 --> 01:27:10,043
were indeed fraudulent, is that correct?

1471
01:27:11,530 --> 01:27:12,380
- That's correct.

1472
01:27:13,790 --> 01:27:14,963
- Thank you Mr. Reese.

1473
01:27:16,010 --> 01:27:17,660
No further questions, Your Honor.

1474
01:27:25,600 --> 01:27:28,250
- I've always heard that
private investigators

1475
01:27:28,250 --> 01:27:31,060
have the keenest sense
of guilt and innocence

1476
01:27:31,060 --> 01:27:34,890
when they do the bidding of
their employers, regardless.

1477
01:27:34,890 --> 01:27:36,723
But they always seem to know the truth.

1478
01:27:37,710 --> 01:27:38,660
- Most of the time.

1479
01:27:40,100 --> 01:27:41,260
- And in the seven years

1480
01:27:41,260 --> 01:27:42,970
that you've worked with
the U.S. Attorneys Office,

1481
01:27:42,970 --> 01:27:45,380
have you ever disagreed
with an assignment?

1482
01:27:45,380 --> 01:27:46,970
- None that I can recall.

1483
01:27:46,970 --> 01:27:48,420
- And how many assignments would you say

1484
01:27:48,420 --> 01:27:51,220
they've given you since working with them?

1485
01:27:51,220 --> 01:27:52,360
- I don't know,

1486
01:27:53,490 --> 01:27:55,580
12 or 10 I guess.

1487
01:27:55,580 --> 01:27:57,080
- And with what I've
read from your records,

1488
01:27:57,080 --> 01:27:59,320
you've always recorded the conversations

1489
01:27:59,320 --> 01:28:01,070
you have with the suspect, correct?

1490
01:28:02,190 --> 01:28:04,040
- The ones that I've talked to, yeah.

1491
01:28:05,110 --> 01:28:06,470
- And how many conversations did you have

1492
01:28:06,470 --> 01:28:07,883
with my client, Mr. Reese?

1493
01:28:11,760 --> 01:28:12,905
- Three.

1494
01:28:12,905 --> 01:28:15,930
- [Blythe] And why didn't you
record those conversations?

1495
01:28:15,930 --> 01:28:19,390
- [Eric] It was at my
discretion, and I chose not to.

1496
01:28:19,390 --> 01:28:20,980
- Fair enough.

1497
01:28:20,980 --> 01:28:24,300
But you also had a conversation
with my client's wife.

1498
01:28:24,300 --> 01:28:26,620
What was said in that conversation,

1499
01:28:26,620 --> 01:28:28,220
which you also failed to record?

1500
01:28:30,790 --> 01:28:32,780
- I tried to convince Carrie Stewart

1501
01:28:32,780 --> 01:28:35,680
to surrender Brian to the Whitaker estate.

1502
01:28:35,680 --> 01:28:38,720
- To which she told you
to go to hell, I assume.

1503
01:28:38,720 --> 01:28:39,820
- Something like that.

1504
01:28:41,700 --> 01:28:43,730
- Did you not tell my client

1505
01:28:43,730 --> 01:28:47,670
that if she were willing to
surrender her parental rights,

1506
01:28:47,670 --> 01:28:50,023
she could avoid a setting like this one?

1507
01:28:51,230 --> 01:28:52,470
- I did.

1508
01:28:52,470 --> 01:28:54,490
- But you're not in a position
to promise such a thing,

1509
01:28:54,490 --> 01:28:56,220
are you Mr. Reese?

1510
01:28:56,220 --> 01:28:57,640
- No.

1511
01:28:57,640 --> 01:29:01,970
- But in your undocumented
conversations with my client,

1512
01:29:01,970 --> 01:29:03,580
you certainly seemed to favor

1513
01:29:03,580 --> 01:29:06,373
my client over your assignment.

1514
01:29:07,320 --> 01:29:09,103
On the evening of September 23rd,

1515
01:29:11,360 --> 01:29:14,617
you told my client, and I quote,

1516
01:29:14,617 --> 01:29:17,167
"You took a child out of a bad situation

1517
01:29:17,167 --> 01:29:19,143
"and provided a better life for him.

1518
01:29:20,007 --> 01:29:22,917
"You're his mother, as
far as I'm concerned."

1519
01:29:26,250 --> 01:29:28,200
Did you not say those words, Mr. Reese?

1520
01:29:30,900 --> 01:29:33,050
Keep in mind, you're
under oath, Mr. Reese.

1521
01:29:35,090 --> 01:29:35,923
- I did.

1522
01:29:37,020 --> 01:29:40,330
- And isn't that contrary to
what your employer believes?

1523
01:29:40,330 --> 01:29:41,400
- Yes.

1524
01:29:41,400 --> 01:29:43,700
- So then it would probably be safe to say

1525
01:29:43,700 --> 01:29:45,500
you don't always agree
with the assignments

1526
01:29:45,500 --> 01:29:47,533
given you by the U.S. Attorneys Office.

1527
01:29:48,490 --> 01:29:49,690
- Correct.

1528
01:29:49,690 --> 01:29:50,900
- Thank you.

1529
01:29:50,900 --> 01:29:52,550
No further questions, Your Honor.

1530
01:29:58,670 --> 01:30:00,240
- And Valerie felt like she was

1531
01:30:00,240 --> 01:30:03,530
finally making a positive
contribution to the world.

1532
01:30:03,530 --> 01:30:06,330
- And you were very proud of her.

1533
01:30:06,330 --> 01:30:10,710
After all she had accomplished
for the past 12 years.

1534
01:30:10,710 --> 01:30:11,543
- Absolutely.

1535
01:30:12,580 --> 01:30:14,210
My only wish is that she were here

1536
01:30:14,210 --> 01:30:16,910
to witness the discovery of her son.

1537
01:30:16,910 --> 01:30:18,263
- Thank you Mr. Whitaker.

1538
01:30:20,440 --> 01:30:22,923
No further questions, Your Honor.

1539
01:30:28,690 --> 01:30:30,410
- Mr. Whitaker.

1540
01:30:30,410 --> 01:30:33,360
Please forgive me, but
my feet are killing me.

1541
01:30:33,360 --> 01:30:35,400
- Whatever makes you
comfortable, Counselor.

1542
01:30:35,400 --> 01:30:36,233
- Thank you.

1543
01:30:37,300 --> 01:30:42,010
So after nine years,
you finally found him.

1544
01:30:42,010 --> 01:30:43,320
What took so long?

1545
01:30:43,320 --> 01:30:45,560
- Your client remained anonymous.

1546
01:30:45,560 --> 01:30:47,530
So we had no trail, no names,

1547
01:30:47,530 --> 01:30:49,610
nothing to even begin on.

1548
01:30:49,610 --> 01:30:52,230
He could've been
anywhere, for all we knew.

1549
01:30:52,230 --> 01:30:54,470
And after a few years of
running around in circles,

1550
01:30:54,470 --> 01:30:56,023
Valerie started to lose hope.

1551
01:30:56,870 --> 01:31:00,470
That's when she turned her
attention to helping others.

1552
01:31:00,470 --> 01:31:01,890
- That's admirable.

1553
01:31:01,890 --> 01:31:03,090
- My daughter desperately tried

1554
01:31:03,090 --> 01:31:04,600
to make up for what she'd done.

1555
01:31:04,600 --> 01:31:06,000
- Sure.

1556
01:31:06,000 --> 01:31:09,420
So when Valerie came home
after serving time in prison,

1557
01:31:09,420 --> 01:31:12,120
what was it that caused
you to take her back in?

1558
01:31:12,120 --> 01:31:13,870
- She expressed how sorry she was,

1559
01:31:13,870 --> 01:31:16,240
and her willingness to
change for the better.

1560
01:31:16,240 --> 01:31:18,790
So my wife and I decided
to support her endeavors

1561
01:31:18,790 --> 01:31:21,190
to campaign, in particular.

1562
01:31:21,190 --> 01:31:23,810
- Were there any
conditions to your support?

1563
01:31:23,810 --> 01:31:26,170
Like there were when you threw her

1564
01:31:26,170 --> 01:31:27,510
out of your home years earlier?

1565
01:31:27,510 --> 01:31:28,710
- Nothing inordinate.

1566
01:31:28,710 --> 01:31:30,840
But she had to abstain from drug use

1567
01:31:30,840 --> 01:31:33,486
and adhere to the rules of our home.

1568
01:31:33,486 --> 01:31:35,580
- But now I'm a little
confused on that, Mr. Whitaker.

1569
01:31:35,580 --> 01:31:37,290
Forgive me, but can you tell me

1570
01:31:37,290 --> 01:31:39,510
what it was that Valerie actually did

1571
01:31:39,510 --> 01:31:41,630
at the age of 17 that caused you

1572
01:31:41,630 --> 01:31:43,350
to put her out of your home?

1573
01:31:43,350 --> 01:31:45,143
- That was nearly 20 years ago.

1574
01:31:46,160 --> 01:31:47,173
I don't remember.

1575
01:31:48,010 --> 01:31:49,890
- You make your only child leave

1576
01:31:49,890 --> 01:31:51,670
the comfort of her own home,

1577
01:31:51,670 --> 01:31:54,250
and you don't remember
what she did to deserve it?

1578
01:31:54,250 --> 01:31:58,160
- Let's just say that Valerie had issues

1579
01:31:58,160 --> 01:32:00,150
long before they became public.

1580
01:32:00,150 --> 01:32:03,230
- God forbid any 17 year
old girl have issues.

1581
01:32:03,230 --> 01:32:04,550
- Objection.

1582
01:32:04,550 --> 01:32:07,830
Your Honor, I don't see what any of this

1583
01:32:07,830 --> 01:32:10,890
has to do with the case?

1584
01:32:10,890 --> 01:32:12,500
- Overruled.

1585
01:32:12,500 --> 01:32:13,900
State your point, Counselor.

1586
01:32:15,480 --> 01:32:18,160
- I guess my concern is

1587
01:32:18,160 --> 01:32:21,300
is you intend to seek custody
of my client's son, correct?

1588
01:32:21,300 --> 01:32:24,820
- We intend to seek
custody of our grandson.

1589
01:32:24,820 --> 01:32:26,040
That is correct.

